docs.abstract: The French behemoth, known for its perfumes, handbags and double-C logo, reported strong sales growth and rising investment. But that it published at all was a surprise.
docs.snippet: The French behemoth, known for its perfumes, handbags and double-C logo, reported strong sales growth and rising investment. But that it published at all was a surprise.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Synonymous with French high fashion and blockbuster Parisian runway shows, Chanel is one of the biggest brands in the global luxury business. Its outrageous octogenarian creative director and the personal style of its chic female founder are the stuff of legend.

headline.main: Chanel Publishes Annual Results for First Time in 108 Years
headline.print_headline: Chanel Upstages Takeover Talk by Showing Its Big Numbers

docs.abstract: Confidential documents reviewed by The Times indicate that Jared Kushner, President Trump’s son-in-law and adviser, probably paid little or no income tax from 2009 to 2016.
docs.snippet: Confidential documents reviewed by The Times indicate that Jared Kushner, President Trump’s son-in-law and adviser, probably paid little or no income tax from 2009 to 2016.
docs.lead_paragraph: Over the past decade, Jared Kushner’s family company has spent billions of dollars buying real estate. His personal stock investments have soared. His net worth has quintupled to almost $324 million.

headline.main: Jared Kushner Paid No Federal Income Tax for Years, Documents Suggest
headline.print_headline: Forms Suggest Kushner Paid Tax Bills of $0

docs.abstract: A legal loophole allows major banks to avoid telling American authorities about certain trading in financial instruments known as derivatives.
docs.snippet: A legal loophole allows major banks to avoid telling American authorities about certain trading in financial instruments known as derivatives.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the maze of subsidiaries that make up Goldman Sachs Group, two in London have nearly identical names: Goldman Sachs International and Goldman Sachs International Bank.

headline.print_headline: Legal Loophole For Derivatives Is Blind Spot For Regulators

docs.abstract: Citigroup had said it was offering a safe haven from high-frequency traders. A Wall Street regulator says the company failed to keep its promise.
docs.snippet: Citigroup had said it was offering a safe haven from high-frequency traders. A Wall Street regulator says the company failed to keep its promise.
docs.lead_paragraph: Citigroup agreed to pay more than $12 million to settle a regulator’s claims that it misled investors who thought they were paying a premium to keep their trading activity shielded from interference by high-frequency traders, the Securities and Exchange Commission has announced.

headline.main: Citigroup to Pay $12 Million Over Accusations It Misled Trading Customers

docs.abstract: When the algorithms that drive social media move on, the children who were separated from their parents remain in detention facilities along the Rio Grande.
docs.snippet: When the algorithms that drive social media move on, the children who were separated from their parents remain in detention facilities along the Rio Grande.
docs.lead_paragraph: BROWNSVILLE, Tex. — After long hours at his day job, Sergio Cordova was driving home to pick up supplies and clothing for the tired and hungry asylum seekers who were camped out just a few miles away, in Matamoros, Mexico, waiting to be let in.

headline.main: At the Border Town That the News Cycle Has Left Behind
headline.print_headline: Checking In At Border, After News Moved On

docs.abstract: Nearly 80 transactions in 2017 totaled $147 million, financial disclosures showed. Ethics experts have said the activity could raise questions of possible conflicts of interest.
docs.snippet: Nearly 80 transactions in 2017 totaled $147 million, financial disclosures showed. Ethics experts have said the activity could raise questions of possible conflicts of interest.
docs.lead_paragraph: Even after they ascended to top White House positions, Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner continued to benefit from an extraordinary number of investment deals carried out by the companies they once ran, ethics filings released Monday evening showed.

headline.main: Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner Had a Busy Year in Investing, Filing Shows
headline.print_headline: Kushner and Wife Disclose $147 Million in Transactions

docs.abstract: The founders of the e-commerce platform believe a stock market model can help level the playing field for high-end items, even if it can’t help average consumers afford them.
docs.snippet: The founders of the e-commerce platform believe a stock market model can help level the playing field for high-end items, even if it can’t help average consumers afford them.
docs.lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Standing among more than 350 pairs of sneakers in his converted attic, Josh Luber, a self-proclaimed “sneakerhead,” held a pair of nearly identical Nike Air Jordan IVs in each hand. He eyed them as if they were rare biological specimens.

headline.main: A Nasdaq for Sneakerheads? StockX Aims to Tame ‘Chaos’ of Luxury Market
headline.print_headline: A Nasdaq for Sneakerheads? A Way to Tame the High-End Market

docs.abstract: President Trump’s son-in-law and senior adviser appears to have paid almost no federal income taxes for several years running.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s son-in-law and senior adviser appears to have paid almost no federal income taxes for several years running.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jared Kushner has a net worth of almost $324 million, and his company has been profitable. But Mr. Kushner, who is President Trump’s son-in-law and senior adviser, appears to have paid almost  no federal income taxes for several years running, according to documents reviewed by The New York Times.

headline.main: How Jared Kushner Avoided Paying Taxes
headline.print_headline: Seven Steps To Avoiding Income Taxes

docs.abstract: The Wall Street bank is betting its brokerage business can help drive growth. Mary Schapiro, who led the S.E.C. from 2009 to 2012, may be a guide.
docs.snippet: The Wall Street bank is betting its brokerage business can help drive growth. Mary Schapiro, who led the S.E.C. from 2009 to 2012, may be a guide.

headline.print_headline: Morgan Stanley Adds Obama-Era S.E.C. Chief To a Position on Its Board
